    <h1>How to Provide Feedback on W3C's CSS Validation Service</h1>

    <p>
      <strong>If your document doesn't validate, and you don't know why,
      or you have a question about the CSS validator.</strong>
    </p>

    <p>
      First, check the <a
      href='http://www.websitedev.de/css/validator-faq'>W3C CSS
      Validator Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</a> to see if your
      question has been answered there. A list of <a
      href='BUGS.html'>reported problems</a> is also available.
    </p>
    <p>
      You have several CSS related mailing lists, so please pick the
      right one before asking a question:
    </p>
    <dl>
      <dt><a
	  href="mailto:www-validator-css@w3.org">www-validator-css@w3.org</a></dt>
      <dd>
	<p>
	  This mailing list is for comments or bug reports on the CSS
	  validator. This is not the right place to ask questions
	  regarding CSS itself.
	</p>
	<p>
	  This mailing list is <em><a
	  href='http://lists.w3.org/Archives/Public/www-validator-css/'>publicly
	  archived</a></em>.
	</p>
	<p>
	  To post messages to www-validator-css@w3.org, you have to be <a
	  href="http://www.w3.org/Mail/Request">subscribed</a>. Messages
	  from non-subscribers are diverted to a human moderator and may
	  (or may not) appear with a delay.
	</p>
      </dd>
      <dt><a href='mailto:www-style@w3.org'>www-style@w3.org</a></dt>
      <dd>
	<p>
	  This mailing list is for <em>technical discussion</em> on <a
	  href="http://www.w3.org/Style/">Web Style Sheets</a>. This is
	  a focused discussion area: all posts to this list must be
	  about style sheets. The list is also the preferred place for
	  discussing <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/">working drafts</a>
	  that are published by W3C's working group on <a
	  href="http://www.w3.org/Style/CSS/">CSS (Cascading Style
	  Sheets)</a>.
	</p>
	<p>
	  This mailing list is <em><a
	  href='http://lists.w3.org/Archives/Public/www-style/'>publicly
	  archived</a></em>.
	</p>
	<p>
	  This list is <em>not</em> for posts of the form "How do
	  I...". For those, please use the Usenet newsgroup <a
	  href="news:comp.infosystems.www.authoring.stylesheets">
	  comp.infosystems.www.authoring.stylesheets</a>, or mailing
	  lists like <a
	  href="http://www.hwg.org/lists/hwg-style">hwg-style</a> (for
	  members of the HTML Writers Guild). <a
	  href="http://www.websitetips.com/css/#newsgroups">Website
	  Tips</a> has links to more fora.
	</p>
	<p>
	  To post messages to www-style@w3.org, you have to be <a
	  href="http://www.w3.org/Mail/Request">subscribed</a>. Messages
	  from non-subscribers are diverted to a human moderator and may
	  appear with a delay.
	</p>
      </dd>
    </dl>

